We can't even get one to stack with a non-rune, because it's  'an old epic'.<br>
<br>
Which three?<br>
Rune5<br>
One of the pop runes (Arcane, I assume?)<br>
The top end berserker series (not a rune, but has considerable damage eating).<br>
All told, about 3kish damage soaking.<br>
<br>
Yes, they get hit more often. Yes, they can use it (and IMO, deserve it). But arguing about the age of the epic having some kind of association to whether it can stack or not is IMO asinine.<br>
I find it similarly irritating that Circle of Seasons and another circle can stack (winter, is it?) but CoS and our post 60 elemental barrier don't. The logic (or lack of it) that is applied to what stacks and what doesn't seems arbitrary at best.<br>
